report.measDesc: The dataset is converted to file geodatabase (FGDB) format using tools in ArcGIS. The geometry is checked, and if needed repaired.
After processing, the dataset is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
The geospatial part of this dataset was created from the populated places polygons from 2010 Census TIGER/Line data. The horizontal positional accuracy is unknown.

prcStep.stepDesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Copied the Data and Maps 2014 U.S. Populated Place Points keeping all cities with a population greater than 10,000 and Montpelier, Vermont. Added the field CAPITAL and calculated its values to "National", "State", or blank. Attached the fields from 2010 Census Summary File 1.

stepSrc.srcDesc: Sources: 1) 2010 Census TIGER/Line Shapefiles; 2) Esri Data; and 3) U.S. Census SF 1.

prcStep.stepDesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Calculated the field PLACEFIPS to include the values of the field STFIPS making PLACEFIPS a unique seven digit number. Deleted the field POP2013. Added the field POPULATION (alias POP2014). Recalculated the field POP_CLASS with the same range breaks.
The following steps were performed by Esri: Deleted the field POP2014. Added the field POPULATION (alias POP2015). Recalculated the field POP_CLASS (based on POPULATION) with the same range breaks.

The following steps were performed by Esri: Joined the fields from Data and Maps 2017 U.S. Census Populated Place Areas. Removed features that didn’t find a match. Calculated the field POPULATION equal to its joined field equivalent and renamed its alias POP2016. Calculated the field POP_CLASS (with the same range breaks) equal to its joined field equivalent.

stepSrc.srcDesc: Sources: 1) 2014 Census TIGER/Line Shapefiles; and 2) Esri Data.

prcStep.stepDesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Joined the fields from Data and Maps 2018 U.S. Census Populated Place Areas. Calculated the field POPULATION equal to its joined field equivalent and renamed its alias POP2017. Calculated the field POP_CLASS (with the same range breaks) equal to its joined field equivalent.
